Add new tests to the AgentDialog test suite to verify that the CWD path is displayed in both the agent-exists and no-agent states.

**File:** `apps/client/src/layers/features/agent-settings/__tests__/AgentDialog.test.tsx`

**Step 1: Add new tests to the existing `describe('AgentDialog', ...)` block:**

```typescript
it('displays CWD path when agent exists', async () => {
  const transport = createMockTransport({
    getAgentByPath: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(mockAgent),
  });
  const Wrapper = createWrapper(transport);

  render(
    <Wrapper>
      <AgentDialog projectPath="/projects/myapp" open={true} onOpenChange={vi.fn()} />
    </Wrapper>
  );

  const dialog = await findDialog();
  // PathBreadcrumb renders the last segments of the path
  // The FolderOpen icon and path breadcrumb should be visible
  expect(within(dialog).getByText('myapp')).toBeInTheDocument();
});

it('displays CWD path when no agent registered', async () => {
  const transport = createMockTransport({
    getAgentByPath: vi.fn().mockResolvedValue(null),
  });
  const Wrapper = createWrapper(transport);

  render(
    <Wrapper>
      <AgentDialog projectPath="/projects/no-agent" open={true} onOpenChange={vi.fn()} />
    </Wrapper>
  );

  // The no-agent state renders in both Dialog and Drawer, so use findAllByText
  const matches = await screen.findAllByText('no-agent');
  expect(matches.length).toBeGreaterThanOrEqual(1);
});
```

Note: `PathBreadcrumb` renders path segments as individual elements. The exact text rendered depends on the `maxSegments` prop and the path structure. For `/projects/myapp` with `maxSegments={3}`, it will render segments like "projects" and "myapp". Test for the last segment ("myapp" or "no-agent") as a simple presence check.

**Acceptance criteria:**
- All existing tests continue to pass
- New test verifies the CWD path segment is visible when an agent exists (via the dialog scoped query)
- New test verifies the CWD path segment is visible when no agent is registered
- Tests use the existing `findDialog()` helper and `createWrapper()` pattern
